  "notes": "Aromanian (Armâneashce/Vlach), Eastern Romance language spoken by the Aromanians in the Balkans (Greece, Albania, North Macedonia, Bulgaria, Serbia). Closely related to Romanian. Central vowel â/î = /ɨ/. Reduced /ə/ vowel ă. No official standardized orthography in most countries.",
